data.title: Bomb!
data.text: Great food. Great customer service. Very friendly. Fried chicken and smothered chicken and all sides were amazing. Huge portions. One portion is enough for 2-3 meals ;)

data.title: Love Dulans!
data.text: I have officially been to ALL of the Dulan's Soul Food Kitchen locations! This one has now ranked the spot of my 2nd favorite location! I came here last Saturday and was IN AND OUT! For those people who know this restaurant chain know that the lines and wait times can most definitely be outrageous but it's worth it! When I arrived I was warmly greeted by all of the employee's and while trying to decide even offered some suggestions! I always think that's an awesome thing to have to provide your customer's! Knowledgeable staff that can make great suggestions on the menu! I went with my normal which is the Smothered Chicken with two sides (Dinner comes with two sides). Mac N Cheese is one of my favorites and I always get a double portion of it! Everything came out fantastic! I have no complaints! You really can't go wrong with the HUGE portions of food that they give you with a reasonable amount of money that they charge! I will be back!

data.title: Better chicken than Roscoe's!
data.text: Fried chicken is an art that Dulan's does very well.  Most places over-cook it, but that is not the case here.  Crispy, delicious, and juicy.  The greens, mashed potatoes, and gravy are very good.  The best side, however, is the red beans and rice.

data.title: Great Food
data.text: The soul food is great and melts in your mouth. My favorite is the beef short ribs. They give me enough food for dinner to ear for 2 days. Don't forget to order peach cobbler. It is to die for!   The service is superb. The dinning room is small and the parking is limited.

data.title: Savory Soul Food
data.text: This is a local favorite of my wife and mine for the most tasteful soul food. Everything is great. We usually place our order by telephone for take-out after church but it's good anytime of the week. The food is excellent, tastes great and the servings are plentiful - worth the price. Parking is better but the lines are still long. We suggest you call ahead as we do. We usually get the Fried Chicken and Turkey Wings dinners  with any of the veggie sides. Included with your order is cornbread muffins, desert and tea in the Sunday meals. We frequent the Manchester and LaBrea restaurant.

data.title: So Good!
data.text: Collectively, we ordered fried chicken, mac and cheese, mashed potato w/gravy and a cabbage and collard green mix. The provided corn break with the meal also. All of it was sooo good!

data.title: Great place for a home cooked meal
data.text: This is a great place for a good, home cooked meal.  When you are in the mood for a good home cooked meal, miss your grandma's cooking, want a Sunday dinner during the week or want a good introduction to soul food, try Soul Food kitchen near the corner of La Brea and Manchester in Inglewood. My favorites are the smothered Chicken (white meat), baked chicken, short ribs, or fish.  For sides they have good Mac N Cheese, Yams, Cabbage and Collard greens. Their cornbread muffins that come with your meal are delicious too!  Makes me hungry just writing this review.  I eat here at least once every month or two.

data.title: Worth waiting for.
data.text: This place is amazing- Be sure to get there early on Sunday afternoon or you will be waiting in a long line.

data.title: quick, delicious, near LAX
data.text: umm umm, and the food was good too! seriously the people there was so incredibly kind and the smoothered chicken was awesome!  collard greens were great and did not have pork in them which i prefer.  it was so easy to get to from LAX, a great alternative to expensive hotel food  when i was stuck in a hotel by the airport- lovely
